    <div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">What is single visit dentistry and how does it work?</span><div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Single visit dentistry uses CEREC CAD/CAM technology to digitally scan, design, mill, and fit crowns, bridges, veneers, and inlays — all in one 90-minute appointment. No impressions, no temporary restorations, no lab wait. Kamakshi Dental is Bengaluru's only clinic offering true single-visit dentistry.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">How is dental implant pricing determined in Bangalore?</span><div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Dental implant pricing at Kamakshi Dental depends on the implant type, bone condition, and complexity. Book a free consultation at your nearest branch for a personalised quote.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">How is Invisalign pricing determined in Bangalore?</span><div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Invisalign treatment in Bangalore at Kamakshi Dental ranges from personalised pricing based on your case.  Free first consultation at all 3 clinics.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">Is root canal treatment painful at Kamakshi Dental?</span><div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">No. Using Waterlase laser technology and modern anaesthesia, root canal treatment at Kamakshi Dental is largely pain-free. Most procedures are completed in a single 60–90 minute appointment. No drills, no repeated visits.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">Which Kamakshi Dental clinic is closest to me?</span><div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Indiranagar (New Tippasandra) serves East Bengaluru — Indiranagar, HAL, Domlur, Koramangala. RR Nagar (BEML Layout) serves West Bengaluru — Nagarbhavi, Kengeri, Uttarahalli. MG Road (Ashok Nagar) serves Central Bengaluru — Brigade Road, Cubbon Park, Commercial Street.</div></div>
      <div class="faq-item" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><div class="faq-q"><span class="faq-q-text">Who is Dr. Akarsh Bilimagga?</span><div class="faq-icon">+</div></div><div class="faq-a">Dr. Akarsh Bilimagga is an MDS specialist in Periodontics and Oral Implantology with 8+ years of experience. He pioneered single-visit CEREC dentistry in Bengaluru and has completed 10,000+ procedures including 2,000+ dental implants. He treats international patients for implants and Invisalign at Kamakshi Dental's 3 Bengaluru clinics.</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

